content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide step-by-step instructions to build it.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has 4 distinct layers
- Base layer: Two red arch-like pieces
- Second layer: One green rectangular block
- Third layer: One yellow rectangular block
- Top layer: Three orange pieces (two triangular pieces on sides and one vertical cylinder in center)

Required blocks and assembly order from bottom to top:

{
Step1: Move block with index 1 (red arch piece, left)
Step2: Move block with index 2 (red arch piece, right)
Step3: Move block with index 4 (green rectangular block)
Step4: Move block with index 6 (yellow rectangular block)
Step5: Move block with index 14 (orange triangular piece, left)
Step6: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular piece, right)
Step7: Move block with index 7 (orange vertical cylinder)
}

The structure will be built from bottom to top, starting with the base arch pieces, then adding the green and yellow blocks as platforms, and finally placing the triangular pieces and cylinder on top. Each block is used exactly as shown in the dictionary without any rotation.
